Definition: causing fear or anxiety by threatening great harm
Example: a dangerous operation; a grave situation; a grave illness; grievous bodily harm; a serious wound; a serious turn of events; a severe case of pneumonia; a life-threatening disease
Synonyms: noun, attribute, dangerousness, grave, grievous, serious, seriousness, severe, severeness, life-threatening, causing, fear, or, anxiety, by, threatening, great, harm, a, operation, situation, illness, bodily, wound, turn, of, events, case, pneumonia, disease
Category: adj.all
